Práctica 3 (IDS Snort 3)
______________________________


1. Introducción y Preparación

sudo su
date

2. Repositorios y Dependencias

dnf config-manager --set-enabled ol9_codeready_builder
dnf install -y epel-release
dnf install -y gcc gcc-c++ make cmake autoconf automake libtool flex bison git wget curl unzip libpcap-devel pcre-devel pcre2-devel libdnet-devel openssl-devel zlib-devel hwloc-devel luajit-devel libuuid-devel pkg-config xz-devel xz

3. Compilación de LibDAQ

cd /tmp
git clone https://github.com/snort3/libdaq.git
cd libdaq
./bootstrap
./configure
make && make install

4. Instalación de Snort 3 y Enlace de Librerías

cd /tmp
wget https://github.com/snort3/snort3/archive/refs/heads/master.zip -O snort3.zip
unzip snort3.zip
cd snort3-master
./configure_cmake.sh --prefix=/usr/local
cd build
make -j$(nproc)
make install

# Registrar las librerías (¡Paso clave!)
echo "/usr/local/lib" > /etc/ld.so.conf.d/local.conf
echo "/usr/local/lib64" >> /etc/ld.so.conf.d/local.conf
ldconfig

5. Configuración del Sistema (Usando Nano)

mkdir -p /etc/snort/rules /var/log/snort
nano /etc/snort/snort.lua


Lua


daq = { module_dirs = { '/usr/local/lib/daq' } }
ips = {
    variables = {
        nets = { HOME_NET = 'any', EXTERNAL_NET = 'any' }
    },
    include = '/etc/snort/rules/local.rules'
}
alert_fast = { }



6. Creación de Reglas Personalizadas

nano /etc/snort/rules/local.rules

📝 Lo que pegas dentro de Nano:




alert icmp any any -> any any (msg:"ICMP Ping detectado"; itype:8; sid:1000001; rev:1;)
alert tcp any any -> any 21 (msg:"Trafico FTP detectado (21)"; flags:S; sid:1000002; rev:1;)
alert tcp any any -> any 22 (msg:"Trafico SSH detectado (22)"; flags:S; sid:1000003; rev:1;)
alert tcp any any -> any 80 (msg:"Trafico HTTP detectado (80)"; flags:S; sid:1000004; rev:1;)
(Guarda con Ctrl+O, Enter, y sal con Ctrl+X)

7. Validación y Escenario de Prueba Limpio

# Validar la configuración

snort -c /etc/snort/snort.lua -T

# Limpiar el log viejo para que el video quede limpio

truncate -s 0 /var/log/snort/alert_fast.txt

# Iniciar Snort con filtro (en la primera ventana)

snort -q -c /etc/snort/snort.lua -i ens160 -A alert_fast -l /var/log/snort "icmp or port 21 or port 22 or port 80"

 En la segunda ventana de Linux (El Monitor):

Bash

tail -f /var/log/snort/alert_fast.txt




